prompt: Write a brief biography of a person named "Brilliant Le Hou". Do not use commas in your reply. Highlight at least 3 sections with markdown, i.e. *highlighted section*. The biography should start with the name of the person.
response: Brilliant Le Hou (born 1971 in Guangxi, China) is an award-winning Chinese documentary filmmaker and short story writer, born and raised in Beijing. Le Hou received her BA from Beijing Normal University, MA from Nanyang Technological University and PhD in Cinema Studies from Nanyang Technological University in 1981. Her research explores Chinese cinema through the prism of memory. Le Hou was featured on "Violin Player", the Hong Kong version of the late Wu Ziying. In 2017, Le Hou won the Silver Bear at the 24th Venice Biennale Film Festival for her feature length documentary on Chinese films and literature, "Wing of Power" (2014). Le Hou won the 2017 International Achievement Award from the Association for Contemporary Cinema (ACAC). Le Hou won the Silver Bear in 2018 from the Chinese Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences at the 30th Asian International Achievement Awards (CHANA). Le Hou received her BA and Ph.D. degrees from the National University of Singapore (NUAS), where she wrote for over 25 years and directed documentaries about Hong Kong cinema and television. Le Hou won the Gold Lion from the Asia Society Cinema Directors Guild Award for Best Direction at the 28th Singapore International Documentary Awards. In 2017 Le Hou received her MSc from National University of Singapore (NUS). Le Hou also holds an MSc and MPhil degrees from the National University of Hong Kong and Nanyang Technological University (NUST), and has presented papers and keynote talks on Hong Kong cinema, video games, and multimedia at numerous conferences, film festivals, and universities around the world.

prompt: Write an essay of at least 900 words on the topic of navigable freeway. Make sure the entire response is in English and no capital letters are used.
response: Navigator Freeway A navigable freeway (NF) is an arterial roadway linking points along an arterial roadway such as highways or arterial railroads, providing access for loading, unloading and passing motorists to destinations including freight yards and distribution points, hospitals and nursing homes. This infrastructure can also provide access for shipping operations such as grain terminals or processing centers, airports or customs processing facilities. There are approximately 175 navigable freeways in the U.S. alone and between 70-90% are built within 50 miles (80 kilometers). Most freeways have two lanes each which provides better circulation between cities than either road system could provide. These freeways also allow the movement of freight through areas with little traffic flow and improve accessibility between urban centers, schools and neighborhoods. These freeways can also reduce congestion between residential communities. prompt:
Kindly summarize the text below in XML format. Make sure the summary contains less than 4 sentences.

Quantum entanglement is the phenomenon that occurs when a group of particles are generated, interact, or share spatial proximity in such a way that the quantum state of each particle of the group cannot be described independently of the state of the others, including when the particles are separated by a large distance. The topic of quantum entanglement is at the heart of the disparity between classical and quantum physics: entanglement is a primary feature of quantum mechanics not present in classical mechanics.

Measurements of physical properties such as position, momentum, spin, and polarization performed on entangled particles can, in some cases, be found to be perfectly correlated. For example, if a pair of entangled particles is generated such that their total spin is known to be zero, and one particle is found to have clockwise spin on a first axis, then the spin of the other particle, measured on the same axis, is found to be anticlockwise. However, this behavior gives rise to seemingly paradoxical effects: any measurement of a particle's properties results in an apparent and irreversible wave function collapse of that particle and changes the original quantum state. With entangled particles, such measurements affect the entangled system as a whole.

Such phenomena were the subject of a 1935 paper by Albert Einstein, Boris Podolsky, and Nathan Rosen, and several papers by Erwin Schrödinger shortly thereafter, describing what came to be known as the EPR paradox. Einstein and others considered such behavior impossible, as it violated the local realism view of causality (Einstein referring to it as "spooky action at a distance") and argued that the accepted formulation of quantum mechanics must therefore be incomplete.
response: Quantum entanglement

prompt: Write a creative and persuasive startup pitch for a business that helps people with chronic illnesses find and manage in-home care. Your pitch should be less than 7 sentences and contain exactly 1 bullet point in markdown.
response: We’ll be your concierge when it’s most convenient and our caregivers are some of the most qualified. Our startup model allows our customers to customize care from any provider you’d like and our medical network has access to doctors nationwide. Our tech platform uses cloud computing, analytics and artificial intelligence to connect our clients with caregivers across the nation and around the globe. Our healthcare technology platform offers an intuitive mobile application with real time health data that’s easily accessible anywhere you are, anytime you need help. Our startup platform uses AI and machine learning to understand patients’ symptoms, behaviors and preferences so our healthcare teams can customize their care accordingly. The startup’s healthcare tech platform provides personalized care management through personalized reminders. This prevents costly crises such as hospitalization and nursing home placement that many chronic illnesses present. It’s simple and straightforward for your patients and our health tech platform’s payment processor helps manage insurance plans for care providers and hospitals. Our pricing structure allows your business to negotiate premium rates from our health insurance carriers for home care providers, nurses and physicians, while maintaining your financial privacy and confidentiality. Our startup’s revenue streams will allow your company to leverage existing networks for referrals from hospitals and physicians and build partnerships with healthcare providers who specialize in chronic conditions. Your healthcare costs are managed through your health technology platform and managed through your preferred health plan providers. You’ll receive personalized care planning tools with personalized alerts about your condition so your health insurance providers know exactly when your treatment needs change and which treatments you’d like. Our startup’s payments processor uses third-party providers such as Humana and PrimeHealthCare, but your patients’ providers pay our healthcare software directly for them. Our healthcare tech platform’s analytics engine analyzes health metrics from our health insurance providers. These analytics engines automatically compute your Medicare Part D spending for services provided at your home and bill your health insurance providers accordingly. This ensures your healthcare costs are accurately monitored and paid for, which results in significant cost savings and patient satisfaction.
